@The Giraffe I’m not denying what you said (as a big Kape fan) but Kape has a better recent resume. Kape is on a 3 fight W streak, Taira on a 2 fight W. Yes, Park was in short notice but even if Taira beat Albazi it would be a 2 fight win streak. All of their wins are by finish (Almabayev is debatable) but Kape deserves it
“We make what the fans want to see” is not the UFC’s motto anymore. Who tf wanted to see Gaethje vs Pimblett for the interim or Volk vs Lopes rematch? Undeserved interim and undeserved title shot. Van vs Taira applies to this situation, I understand what giraffe said but arguably Dana wants an asian champion to grow their audience.
@Great (Again, without bias) Imo Kape beats both of them and Taira beats Van. I do not like Josh Van at all but both of them would beat him anyways

